the target closure's class can be called from the helper since they're in the same package, but different classloaders? Since they are in the same classloader, that makes sense. I need to clarify why I might get an error with \\\"cannot find symbol variable.\\\" It turns out that Java can reference classes with names containing a \\\"$\\\" if they're in the same package.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented focused coverage for the active dynamic-access class.\n\nAdded:\n\n- `tests/src/io.rest-assured/rest-assured/5.5.0/src/test/java/io_rest_assured/rest_assured/RestAssuredHttpBuilderGroovyHelperInner_createClosureThatCalls_closure2Test.java`\n  - Dedicated public test class for `RestAssuredHttpBuilderGroovyHelper$_createClosureThatCalls_closure2`.\n  - Exercises the compiler-generated `class$` resolver so execution reaches `Class.forName(String)`.\n  - Includes Native Image unsupported-feature handling consistent with existing tests.\n\n- `tests/src/io.rest-assured/rest-assured/5.5.0/src/test/java/io/restassured/internal/RestAssuredHttpBuilderGroovyHelperCreateClosureThatCallsClosure2DirectAccess.java`\n  - Small direct-access helper used to call the package-private Groovy-generated `class$` method without reflection.\n\nI did not run or compile tests, per instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_073d866382d64679016a019861898081949b5a7a90d2d4bbe1\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 779, "output": 707, "cacheRead": 62976, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 64462, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1778489426995, "responseId": "resp_073d866382d64679016a019853b57881948eaf1a6eb648ceeb"}, "toolResults": []}
