[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering error handling**\n\nIt looks like we might need to make some changes to our error handling process. Specifically, I think we should handle `LinkageError` in our tests, similar to how we manage `statusLine`. Since tests run under Native Image by default, adding catches for `LinkageError` before general `Error` will make sense. Otherwise, current catch statements will only address unsupported features, which could lead to other init errors from Groovy not being caught. I should ensure the test adheres to the existing patterns.\n\n**Evaluating error handling**\n\nI’m noticing that the existing pattern doesn’t use assertThrows. Instead, it catches NoClassDefFoundError manually and checks if it’s a native failure. I think we should reflect that to help distinguish between cases. For the missing class, NoClassDefFoundError could point to an expected class that's missing or an initialization failure. It feels like I should edit this manual check. Also, does this class need any running? I'll figure that out!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_073d866382d64679016a019b4327fc8194985a3419e655c19c\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqAZtQo5vPmQAYFKzJ96u7vzujMXdZXwSbkZ9T5SLRgQReAOZfQ-ScH__feuKd4LYhYUKD55ZqYrhYjmIlgQ5TZZ-nv1F0L8WV9YT5AZVdz0KGfx92j-Yiev0S8617Tv_IgXRj0sToKQlnTA0qhDonqpwR67ovoHrZp_nfEZtBi43qjFc12JYgd6RtDmhYlhWd7PT3zd9WAZMWYBtIeDwxR_T_iz_-jKQ_FXuByTL7rbBypQ8XUJShyqjzu8CAuSTVdQVqwrQZrvcCcEm2Q8t13SFQ9AsDQlG4Z6GWJZq5AvacZE_TaMbNZHqpau2PjdA6ZSqy5orlStQXZJvR8ToDX4mruCZf8D95FvMn-Gl6qE6Ls5Ekz95p_h5DpsDtL2NCike-mm18chR8eoPxSZbsA2uejkubhYHKRCu6AGceW8a9QS08ExWj_N5QjT1yXfz9C5LwW2AN9YaTYKvReKpbbuzwJyof7xCDzjnf1o_qLsL6Y42L223x6R45c-h8PgysHNU7W8ixBJVTTQTsng3K8NuQxAwuIzz3rvqOC-u4bJiG3Nc9S4uo_VmmRRkOsnQQL_0se3XOjd6pcaxcaLRu6keOzyBIyk76xmBY3XTZA3RqSNjujN1OQIQzpPazdKRpIJ6HwoM9c5JZo_WYRFwRfavXbarjLQTNQNhHKJ5BN5WSOv7swcd95RJ-JyFFYXxrH5JrDKETiEJQdO